1.16.5.1.16.5-2.0.24:
- Dropped support for Minecraft 1.16.4
- A general performance / memory usage improvement version
- Align ourself with the modified multiblock API from ZeroCore
- New Fuel Rods rendering system. Expanding on the previous custom-model based system, now the fuel/waste levels are rendered along the the Fuel Rod model itself, removing the need of a Tile Entity Special Renderer, speeding things up quite a bit. The custom models are cached and created only when needed. Occlusion detection still in place, so no quads will be rendered if a Fuel Rod is surrounded be opaque blocks (or if there is no glass in the Reactor walls)
- General speed and memory optimizations in the whole codebase
- Fix Computer API reporting an incorrect value from getNumberOfControlRods(). Close #48
- Bumped version to 2.0.24
- Updated Minecraft to version 1.16.5
- Updated Forge to version 36.2.0
